  "notes": [
    "1926-27 and 1929-30: no league held; 1941-45: league suspended (WWII), so 1942-1945 absent.",
    "1936 (1935-36): no final played; Mayo champions on league points (runner_up null).",
    "2020 and 2021: no Division 1 final (2020 round-robin; 2021 Dublin and Kerry shared) - both absent from finals.",
    "New York contested several overall finals (winners 1950, 1964, 1967); a separate 'home final' among Irish counties was also played those years.",
    "Several finals went to replays/penalties (e.g. 2024 Derry beat Dublin on penalties); the decisive result is reported.",
    "division1_semifinalists: many seasons had NO top-division semi-final (decided on league points, group/round-robin with the top two going straight to the final, or final-only) and are absent here; from 2017 the NFL abolished semi-finals. New York 'home final' years list the beaten home-semi-finalists where sourced. Coverage is partial for some 1930s-60s and a few later seasons (e.g. 1992) whose per-season articles lack a knockout section, and for 2001/2005 only one of the two beaten semi-finalists could be sourced. As the third tier is worth only 0.5, these gaps have negligible effect on standings.",
    "lower_division_champions: cleaned to a flat list of winning counties per year. Division 2 recorded from 1999; Divisions 3-4 from 2008. Shared/joint titles list both counties (1999 Kerry & Sligo as Div 2A/2B; 2021 Div 2 Kildare & Mayo and Div 4 Antrim & Louth shared due to COVID fixture clashes). Pre-1999 lower-division (old two-division era) winners were not collected in this pass."
